caption: Food was average, underwhelming and definitely overpriced. Staff seemed unequipped to handle a weekday crowd. Also, the bathroom (and surrounding tables) smelled like a sewer pipe blew out.

I loved it First off, staff is Amazing. After a road trip through SC, GA and Florida the staff here was hands down the friendliest (and truthfully, the cutest !). The service was A+ all around. The $5 Mule on Mondays ? Amazing. Seriously. The apps for 25% off on Monday? Not bad ! We had the wings and veggies. I actually had the Quinea salad and it was super delicious. Loved it ao much we literally cant wait to go back ! Run there and see for yourself !

Delicious, well-prepared dishes and exceptional service! Definitely recommend the loaded tots and the "Best Damn Prime Rib Sandwich." It's sliced tender prime rib, melted gruyere, caramelized onions, horseradish aioli, served on toasted ciabatta. It normally comes with seasoned waffle fries. I choose the Brussels sprouts instead.  The outdoor seating is perfect. The crafted cocktails are over-the-top!

The staff is amazing, Shay, Sal, Anisa, Olivia, Kailyn, and the rest of the staff here are top notch! The service is the best in town, and the food and drinks are spectacular. I would highly recommend this restaurant!

The atmosphere here is awesome. The staff was friendly. The food did take a while to come out however, it was a busy Saturday night and our waitress did give us a heads up. I ordered the prime rib steak. Great presentation, very tasty and cooked perfectly. Their drinks were a little pricey. Will come back for their other dinner dishes and also for brunch.
Great atmosphere, friendly service and fresh tasty food! Went for happy hour and they have great deals.
Great brunch, will definitely be back!
Great food and great drinks! The service was phenomenal. This is a definite recommend from me. Go visit this place and enjoy an outstanding dinner or just some delicious drinks.

This place is fantastic! The g'morning burger is super good, I recommend you add avocado. The food is presented beautifully, and is super tasty. I wish OAK had been around back in my day in Gainesville! Everything we ordered to eat was excellent (I did the steak - beauty!) the drinks were great and they had an awesome selection of specialty cocktails and a real nice beer wall as well. Staff was super friendly and the overall atmosphere was just really cool. We were there on a Monday and they had a $5 Monday Moscow Mule deal going on so we took advantage of that and ended up hanging out there way longer than we meant to!

Sat at the bar, ended up having the best experience! Had the lamb pops with mash and truffle mac and cheese. I didn't skip on dessert either, delicious banana bread carried me into a lovely food coma with some light and kind conversation with bartenders Kasi and Michaela. Good choices were made!!!

But, you should have known that) and Kate were fantastic. Their colleagues “Green Day” and “The Suffocator”, were great too. Ashley and a cast of other amazing team members made this the location I will come back to at some point in the future.  Just kidding about the inside jokes above.  I highly recommend enjoy a Sunday morning at this awesome establishment.

A must see, when visiting Gainesville! Great ambiance and awesome food . Fair prices . Fresh ingredients. Nice staff.relaxing but also vibrant .  I went to Gainesville on a  day trip and visited this place twice because of how good the food/drinks /staff were ! Thanks a great time .

We came with no expectations and left having had a great experience. We ordered three meals and each was exceptional. I could go into detail about each dish, but that could take a page or two. Suffice it to say that everything was cooked to perfection from the steak fillet and asparagus, to the pasta, kale, and lamb.  It was wonderful. The entire staff was friendly and our waitress was delightful.  This is a "go again" for us!  We got there early... Hence the empty restaurant pictures. It was filling up as we left.

This is a typical American style brunch place. They have all the staples with a couple of unique features, like eggs benedict with steak. The steak was cooked perfectly, but the hollandaise sauce was too runny and made the biscuit soggy. Breakfast potatoes were cooked well with a crispiness on the outside and soft potato on the inside. Drinks were good, if a bit diluted. Prices were fair considering the location. Service was excellent! Our waitress even split the dessert amongst the 2 people who got it without being asked. Nice rustic decor and ambiance.  Edit: I came back and was disappointed. The chicken and waffles that I had thought was such a great deal for the amount of chicken you got was just a one-off thing. This time, the chicken was about 1/3 of the size from last time. I don't like that inconsistency in serving sizes. Also, it took us much longer to get our food this time. On the bright side, I tried the Orange Blossom Mimosa and it was delicious!

Brunch at Oak is a must-do in Gainesville. It opens at 11 and be sure you make a reservation. Bottomless mimosas and plentiful food blend with great atmosphere to create a truly wonderful experience. While the menu could use a few more lunch-type items, you’re sure to find something you’ll enjoy. In our party we sampled Bananas Foster French Toast, Strawberry Pancakes, and a breakfast platter of bacon and eggs. All were well-prepared and delicious. Service was excellent.

Will not be back here. I made a reservation a week in advance only to be told upon arrival that all the seats inside were taken and we would have to sit outside (And it was a bit chilly). Our table was right next to the bar and I had trouble talking to my family over the loud drunk people. One of the people had a dog and WHILE WE WERE EATING the dog was jumping all over us and going under our stools. Staff said noting. Additionally for the two hours we were there we saw our waitress maybe four times. Getting drinks refilled and sauces ect was nearly impossible. Lastly the food. Delicious... mostly. WAYY over priced. My dad found multiple shrimp peels in his shrimp and grits, and the lettuce on my salad was burnt and wilted. (They grill the lettuce for extra flavor, but mine tasted like only ash)  The quality did not match the price, and additionally the price did not match the service. Overall not worth it.

My boyfriend recently moved to Gainesville and OAK became a fast favorite to us. The service and food is always delicious. The only downside that i’ve found is the wine. There’s not a very big selection but the items they do carry are pretty good. However, the pours here are way below average, if I’m paying 7.99 for a glass of a 10.99 bottle of wine, I expect to have a decent pour or at least a portion controlled amount. The pours are always freehanded and filled less than half way in a very tiny glass. I’d be more than happy to order multiple glasses but it just doesn’t make sense for what you get. I think a little portion control for the bartenders using mini decanters could go a long way. This is the only reason I brought my 4 star review down to a 3.

Bigger portions would warrant the premium you pay for the food. But since the portions really aren’t that big, you don’t get that much for what you pay. $27 for what is essentially a scoop of mashed potatoes, a few pieces of asparagus, and a steak medallion at best. We wanted to try something other than Harry’s which has gotten boring, but here I am with hunger in my belly after a $30 entree. Probably won’t be back soon. The service and taste were excellent, however.
Wait staff was nice and food was good, but bottomless mimosas were slow to refill.
Nice app selection. Good draughts. Full bar, cocktails and bourbons available.
Expensive, but beautiful atmosphere, great service, and delicious food.

Had a great waitress but the kitchen made a terrible steak 2 times in a row (had a friend try it to validate) refused to take it off my tab and then tried to kick us out. Terrible place. Bad food. And horrible customer service.
A must to go to place while in Gainesville visiting my daughter. Great food, drinks and service. Fun, relaxed atmosphere with class!
Love it

Their drinks were so delicious and flavorful. I had the southern Belle and it did not disappoint. I also had the cauliflower wings which were also very good.  The service was pretty bad. My coworker ordered a drink at the same time I did and it came when I was almost done with mine. They also forgot to put his food order in. I was disappointed with the service.

The atmosphere, server (Blair), dinner, cocktails and dessert were all wonderful. It was a really comfortable place and they have different specials every night that change weekly.  Will definitely go back!
Nice food and good drinks but bring your wallet because it is pricey

Seems to be a constantly changing menu. The fried pimento balls is way too dank. Def worth getting the beer card for the wall. You don't have to dress too formally but expect a nicer experience. Not the quickest service.
Good food, decent price. Beer selection was limited but nice. Buffalo cauliflower will keep me coming back !

I'm torn about this place. Their happy hour is fantastic, great deals on drinks and appetizers. The appetizers we ordered were really good - I ordered the pretzel and my husband ordered wings. A few other things were ordered by friends, the fried green tomato tower looked amazing. The service was where there were issues. Part of HH on Fridays is free bacon, which was never mentioned by our server, but a friend asked for it and was assured it would come. It never came. Then during checkout there were issues with two of our friends' bills. Without going into details, cards were charged the wrong amount multiple times with minimal apology. Annoying to say the least.

OAK (must) invest in sound dampening. The place hits over 90 DB making any conversation impossible.  However, as of July 2018, they have a better menu with more wines and more creative food. The space has a cool downtown vibe with an open wall facing first street.  Honestly, the food was not incredible, it was good enough, but the service and ambience made up for it.  The service was solid and our sever did a fantastic job of juggling multiple tables despite a Saturday onslaught.  I had the lamb, which was good, despite being very rare (I ordered medium). The charcuterie platter was superb. The restaurant would be best for a informal cocktail and bar food meet-up. I will go back!

This is my absolute favorite bar stop in Gainesville for sure. It's so calming in there, the environment alone is worth the 5 stars. Calming, indirect, dim lighting, and the main decore is wood. The drinks have never, ever, been bad. They nail whatever off the wall drink I ask for every single time without fail. The food is fantastic and their brunch is absolutely to die for.
Hidden gem in downtown Gainesville!  Will definitely be back!
Nice place , really cold beer , funny karaoke , very good service
Our server was great. The prime rib sliders were amazing.

The interior of the dinner felt very modern with the winding wooden paths and mirrored walls giving the space a warm and open feel but the lack of carpeting caused noise to be abundant. The service was ok; our waitress was very nice and friendly and the mimosas were refilled very quickly but our food took nearly half an hour to come out due to a large group that was also there. The food itself was presented very nicely but I don't think it merited such a high cost for it. I don't regret going but I don't think I'd go again unless you'd want bottomless mimosas on the weekend.

Went to this restaurant for their brunch. The food was good, but not excellent and the servers were very nice. They only have plain hot coffee.The food took a long time to come out, most likely because of a very large party in the resteraunt. Some people in my party got the bottomless mimosas offered on Saturdays and Sundays, which they were very good about filling up. I wouldn't recommend this place but I can't say it was bad either.
I would give the place zero stars if it were possible.  Sat there for 20 minutes being ignored and finally walked out. The staff is really bad.
Pretty good food, but service was terrible.
Good service, great food, fun atmosphere
Christa the manager does a super job
Very nice staff.  Good drinks and food.
Friendly staff, and great drinks, but the food just wasn't great for what you pay for

Grilled chrese & tomato soup w/FIFA on screen...awesome!
Good happy hour, tasty cocktails and delicious food
Great place!!! Indoor outdoor.  So muchfun
Service was slow and waiter seemed disengaged. Food was pretty good.
Great atmosphere, drinks and food!
Love it! Great food, drinks, service! Beautiful atmosphere!
Love this place! Great atmosphere! Get the loaded tots, amazing omg! Will return again
The food here is tasty and different, although I was put off by their high prices and small menu.
Food was good but the service was bad...

Their service has gotten much better. The price of some of their meals it's a bit high but I've never had much of a wait for anything there.  The bottomless mimosas definitely add to the brunching experience.
They have the best drinks in town hands down! The drink prices aren't too bad either. I love the mousse that they have for the drinks. This is my go-to bar for a great time.

This place is great, wait times aren't too bad (pretty on par for downtown Gainesville), and they have great food and options. The buffalo cauliflower is great! Come here for your birthday for a photo-worthy drink on the house
Very nice. Staff was friendly. Food was tasty. Some surprising choices. I'll go again when in the area.
Great craft cocktails, yummy fried green tomato and pimento cheese stack, and ooey gooey grilled cheese with tomato soup! Yum!

I have been here a few times and today we went specifically for ladies night. Online it was advertised as 5 dollar cocktails. When we arrived at 7 they told us it didn't start until 8. Not a big deal even though their website did not specify it just said Thursday. Then 8 o'clock came and they said ladies night didnt start until 9. We then showed them their website listing the special to which the female manager responded by saying it was our phones displaying it incorrectly and walked away. I went back to check after we left and they had changed their ad online. You should honor what you advertise and learn to give better customer service. What a rude manager we won't be returning.
Very good flank steak.  These guys know how to do a flank steak!
Slow service. Mediocre food. Nice ambiance

This is my favorite place to dine on special occasions. Their food and drink menu are amazing. I love the atmosphere. Service is typically good too. I have had a few experiences over the years where the service was slow and apathetic when it should not have been. Overall, I recommend going!
Delicious fried oreos and fun atmosphere
Amazing food and beautiful location

I was so pleased with the atmosphere, the food, and the service here! Major props to the chef - our small appetizer totally satisfied our hunger (so yummy and filling!) and the fried Oreos were a sweet way to end the evening!
The flavors for all the good ordered was great
The layout and decor are nice, the service was good, and the food wasn't bad at all.
The food is great!! The price tag isn't!!
Delicious drinks, good food, but the service isn't great and it's always unbearably loud.

Small menu but good food! They also have great drinks with a cool atmosphere. Great patio seating for nice weather. I recommend the southern belle cocktail (its awesome). They also host trivia nights-check out their FB page for the weekly theme.

Had the BBQ Tofu Slider. Was a bit unsure about how it would turn out, because it sounded a bit too dry. But it turned out to be well balanced and pretty tasty!  The service is okay. A bit on the slower side, but decent for a bar.  Had a good time overall.
So tasty! And bottomless mimosas and rum punch. :) our sever Angela was super nice. Great visit
Horrible

Came for brunch on a Saturday, and it was amazing! I dragged my parents along, who usually breakfast at places like Waffle House, and they are converted!  I has the Eggs Benedict with sirloin tips, which was very tasty, a blackberry bourbon lemonade, and the sweet potato creme brulee. Wow. I haven't had a meal so good in Gainesville for a long time. My dad, a native Alabaman, was very impressed with the shrimp and grits, and my mom got the seasonal vegetarian quiche, which she said was delicious.  I'd recommend this spot for anyone looking for a modern southern meal. Can't say enough good things about OAK, and I hope they continue their success!
Not a lot of lunch options. But it was a very beautiful place.

Nice decor, food over-priced and not all that great. Pretentious nouveau southern falls flat. Drinks are yummy, service leaves something to be desired ... Namely, service. Strikes me as more of a hang-out for college kids late night than an actual serious restaurant.

Portion size was good and quality of food was excellent but can you give me a larger glass for my water.  Felt like i was in kindergarten with my 8oz water glass. Decor was nice and staff was friendly.  A little overpriced for some items but i guess you are paying that due to location of restaurant.  Overall a good experience
Great place, great food!
Great ambient, tasty beers and the best American Food in town.
Really good drinks.

Great food for the price

Love the variety of food.  Staff is friendly and attentive.  High energy place with a good bar and gaming area.
